!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

consult /kənˈsʌlt/

(consulting,consulted,consults) 

1. V-T/V-I If you consult an expert or someone senior to you or consult with them, you ask them for their opinion, advice, or permission. 咨询 

例： Consult your doctor about how much exercise you should get. 咨询你的医生你应做多少运动。 

例： He needed to consult with an attorney. 他需要和律师咨询。 

2. V-T If you consult a book or a map, you look in it or look at it in order to find some information. 查阅 

例： Consult the chart on page 44 for the correct cooking times. 查阅第44页的图表找正确的烹调时间。 

3. V-RECIP If a person or group of people consults with other people or consults them, or if two people or groups consult , they talk and exchange ideas and opinions about what they might decide to do. 商量 

例： After consulting with her daughter and manager, she decided to take on the part, on her terms. 同她的女儿兼经纪人商量之后，她决定按她的要求接受那个角色。 

例： The two countries will have to consult their allies. 两国得同各自的盟友协商。

</div>

